3:["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Drift settles funding rates every hour using a time-weighted average of the mark price deviation from the index price over the funding period. The protocol's vAMM provides continuous liquidity while the DLOB handles large orders, creating dynamic funding conditions. Insurance fund backing helps stabilize funding calculations during extreme market conditions. JIT liquidity auctions can influence short-term funding rates by providing additional liquidity exactly when needed."}]
4:["$","section",null,{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":["Why ","BONK","/","USDT","?"]}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"BONK's status as a leading Solana meme coin creates distinct funding patterns driven by retail sentiment and social media cycles. The pair often exhibits asymmetric funding behavior, with higher positive rates during rallies as retail traders favor long positions. Mid-tier volume provides sufficient liquidity for arbitrage while maintaining rate volatility that creates profitable opportunities."}]]}]
5:["$","section","0",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Historical Funding Rate Patterns"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"BONK/USDT funding rates on Drift typically range from -0.1% to +0.3% per hour during normal conditions, with extreme events pushing rates above 1% hourly. Positive rates dominate during meme coin hype cycles, often sustained for 12-24 hour periods. Weekend periods frequently show elevated rates as retail activity peaks while institutional arbitrage decreases. The hourly settlement creates 24 opportunities per day, allowing for granular position management compared to 8-hour funding cycles elsewhere."}]]}]
6:["$","section","1",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Arbitrage Opportunities and Execution"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Cross-DEX arbitrage between Drift and Solana perpetual platforms like Mango or Phoenix can be highly profitable during funding rate divergences. The 1-hour funding cycle allows for rapid position adjustments when rates exceed 0.1% hourly equivalent. JIT liquidity auctions provide opportunities to enter positions at favorable prices right before funding settlement. Automated strategies can capitalize on the predictable hourly timing while managing Solana network congestion during high-activity periods."}]]}]
7:["$","section","2",{"className":"mb-10","children":[["$","h2",null,{"className":"text-2xl font-extrabold tracking-tight text-foreground mt-12 mb-4","style":{"fontFamily":"var(--font-montserrat), sans-serif"},"children":"Risk Considerations and Limitations"}],["$","p",null,{"className":"text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed","children":"Solana network dependency creates execution risk during congestion, potentially preventing timely position adjustments before funding deadlines. BONK's high volatility can generate significant unrealized losses that offset funding income if not properly hedged. Lower liquidity compared to centralized exchanges means larger position sizes may experience slippage that erodes arbitrage profits. Drift's complex liquidation mechanics using the DLOB system require careful margin management, especially for leveraged funding rate strategies."}]]}]
8:["$","$Ld",null,{"items":[{"question":"How often does BONK funding settle on Drift?","answer":"BONK/USDT funding rates on Drift settle every hour, providing 24 funding events per day. This frequent settlement allows for more responsive arbitrage strategies compared to traditional 8-hour cycles on other exchanges."},{"question":"What makes BONK funding rates different from other meme coins?","answer":"BONK funding rates tend to be more volatile and skewed positive during retail activity periods due to its status as Solana's leading meme coin. The combination of retail sentiment and Solana ecosystem activity creates unique funding patterns not seen in Ethereum-based meme coins."},{"question":"Can Solana network issues affect funding rate arbitrage?","answer":"Yes, Solana network congestion can prevent timely position entry or exit before funding settlement, creating execution risk. Traders should monitor network health and consider maintaining positions slightly longer than the 1-hour cycle to account for potential delays."},{"question":"How does Drift's JIT liquidity affect BONK funding rates?","answer":"JIT liquidity auctions can temporarily reduce funding rates by providing additional liquidity exactly when large orders create price pressure. This mechanism can dampen extreme funding spikes but also creates opportunities for savvy traders to time their entries around auction periods."}]}]
